        <a name="systemRequirements"></a>
        <h2>System requirements</h2>

        <p>Esri Maps for SharePoint requires an account that is part of an <a href="http://help.arcgis.com/en/arcgisonline/help/#/What_is_ArcGIS_Online/010q00000074000000/">ArcGIS Online</a> organization and Microsoft SharePoint 2010 or 2013 Foundation, Server Standard, or Server Enterprise edition.</p>


        <h3>Supported languages</h3>
        <p>(Coming soon) Arabic, Chinese (Simplified), English, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Portuguese (Brazil), Russian, and Spanish.</p>


        <a name="whatsNew"></a>
        <h2>What's new</h2>
        <p>Esri Maps for SharePoint version 3.0 was released in July 2013. It includes the following updates and enhancements:</p>
        <ul>
        <li>New product name—Esri Maps for SharePoint</li>
	<li>Support for SharePoint 2010 and SharePoint 2013 (on-premises)</li>
	<li>Updated ArcGIS Map Web Part—Silverlight-based web part updated for SharePoint 2010 and SharePoint 2013 (on-premises).</li>
        <li>Initial release of Esri Maps Web Part—JavaScript-based web part supported in SharePoint 2010 and SharePoint 2013 (on-premises).</li>
	<li>Tighter integration with ArcGIS Online</li>
	<li>Portal for ArcGIS 10.2 support</li>
	<li>External data connectivity via SharePoint Business Connectivity Services (BCS)</li>
	<li>Web Part-to-Web Part connections (Esri Maps Web Part to a List Web Part) </li>
	<li>Updated to support the ArcGIS for Silverlight v3.1 and ArcGIS Extensibility v3.1 SDKs (Silverlight-based map web part only)</li>
        </ul>


